"Martínez-Blanco J., Colón J., Gabarrell X., Font X., Sánchez A., Artola A., Rieradevall J.","The use of life cycle assessment for the comparison of biowaste composting at home and full scale",2010,"Waste Management","30","6",,"983","994",,,10.1016/j.wasman.2010.02.023,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77951253325&partnerID=40&md5=6922c05acefddbdab46cfa725564a08d","SosteniPrA Research Group, Institute of Environmental Science and Technology (ICTA), Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici C Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain; Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain; Composting Research Group (GICOM), Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona (UAB), 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain","Martínez-Blanco, J., SosteniPrA Research Group, Institute of Environmental Science and Technology (ICTA), Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici C Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain; Colón, J., Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain, Composting Research Group (GICOM), Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona (UAB), 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain; Gabarrell, X., SosteniPrA Research Group, Institute of Environmental Science and Technology (ICTA), Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici C Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain, Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain; Font, X., Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain, Composting Research Group (GICOM), Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona (UAB), 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain; Sánchez, A., Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain, Composting Research Group (GICOM), Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona (UAB), 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain; Artola, A., Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain, Composting Research Group (GICOM), Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona (UAB), 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain; Rieradevall, J., SosteniPrA Research Group, Institute of Environmental Science and Technology (ICTA), Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici C Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain, Department of Chemical Engineering, Universitat Autònoma de Barcelona, 08193 Edifici Q Bellaterra (Barcelona), Spain","Environmental impacts and gaseous emissions associated to home and industrial composting of the source-separated organic fraction of municipal solid waste have been evaluated using the environmental tool of life cycle assessment (LCA). Experimental data of both scenarios were experimentally collected. The functional unit used was one ton of organic waste. Ammonia, methane and nitrous oxide released from home composting (HC) were more than five times higher than those of industrial composting (IC) but the latter involved within 2 and 53 times more consumption or generation of transport, energy, water, infrastructures, waste and Volatile Organic Compounds (VOCs) emissions than HC. Therefore, results indicated that IC was more impacting than HC for four of the impact categories considered (abiotic depletion, ozone layer depletion, photochemical oxidation and cumulative energy demand) and less impacting for the other three (acidification, eutrophication and global warming). Production of composting bin and gaseous emissions are the main responsible for the HC impacts, whereas for IC the main contributions come from collection and transportation of organic waste, electricity consumption, dumped waste and VOCs emission. These results suggest that HC may be an interesting alternative or complement to IC in low density areas of population. © 2010 Elsevier Ltd.",,"Abiotic depletion; Biowaste composting; Composting bin; Cumulative energy demands; Electricity-consumption; Experimental data; Full scale; Functional units; Gaseous emissions; Life-cycle assessments; Low density; Nitrous oxide; Organic fraction of municipal solid wastes; Organic wastes; Ozone layer depletion; Photochemical oxidation; Energy conversion; Environmental impact; Eutrophication; Global warming; Industrial emissions; Life cycle; Methane; Nitrogen oxides; Ozone; Ozone layer; Sewage; Solid wastes; Volatile organic compounds; Waste treatment; ammonia; methane; nitrous oxide; volatile organic compound; water; ammonia; composting; environmental impact assessment; industrial emission; life cycle analysis; methane; municipal solid waste; nitrous oxide; volatile organic compound; waste management; acidification; article; composting; controlled study; electricity; energy; environmental impact; eutrophication; gas; greenhouse effect; home; life cycle; municipal solid waste; organic waste; ozone depletion; photooxidation; priority journal; waste disposal; Environmental Monitoring; Gases; Global Warming; Industry; Organic Chemicals; Refuse Disposal; Volatile Organic Compounds",,"ammonia, 14798-03-9, 51847-23-5, 7664-41-7; methane, 74-82-8; nitrous oxide, 10024-97-2; water, 7732-18-5; Gases; Organic Chemicals; Volatile Organic Compounds",,,,"Althaus, H.-J., Chudacoff, M., Hellweg, S., Hischier, R., Jungbluth, N., Osses, M., Primas, A., (2004) Life Cycle Inventories of Chemicals. Ecoinvent Report Number 8, , Swiss Centre for Life Cycle Inventories, Dübendorf, Switzerland; Amlinger, F., Peyr, S., Cuhls, C., Greenhouse gas emissions from composting and mechanical biological treatment (2008) Waste Management and Research, 26 (1), pp. 47-60; Ansorena, J., Composting in Guipuzkoa (2008) RETEMA, 128, pp. 34-43. , (in Spanish